  "title": "Volunteer Management Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Volunteer Management Executive</strong></p>\n<p>Location: Jurong West / Bedok</p>\n<p>Employment Type: Full-Time</p>\n<p>Reports To: AM, Prevention</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p><u><strong>Volunteer Recruitment &amp; Engagement</strong></u></p>\n<p>• Manage volunteer recruitment, interview screening &amp; onboarding</p>\n<p>• Maintain volunteer database, schedules &amp; deployment plans</p>\n<p>• Coordinate volunteer orientations, briefings &amp; handbook adherence</p>\n<p>• Build strong volunteer culture aligned with trauma‑informed values</p>\n<p><u><strong>Programme Support</strong></u></p>\n<p>• Support shelter, events, outreach and community programmes</p>\n<p>• Coordinate volunteer logistics, communications &amp; duty fulfilment</p>\n<p>• Track volunteer hours, attendance &amp; feedback</p>\n<p><u><strong>Training &amp; Capacity Building</strong></u></p>\n<p>• Conduct briefings on safeguarding, confidentiality, boundaries &amp; crisis response</p>\n<p>• Coordinate training sessions and capability development</p>\n<p><u><strong>Administrative &amp; Reporting</strong></u></p>\n<p>• Maintain volunteer records &amp; compliance with safeguarding policies</p>\n<p>• Support reporting to management &amp; funding partners</p>\n<p>• Improve volunteer processes &amp; experience feedback loops</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u></p>\n<p>• Diploma/Degree in Social Sciences, Community Development, Communications or related field</p>\n<p>• Experience in volunteer or community engagement preferred</p>\n<p>• Strong interpersonal, communication &amp; organisation skills</p>\n<p>• Compassionate, adaptable, and aligned with social‑service values</p>\n<p>• Respect for confidentiality &amp; sensitivity when engaging with survivors</p>",
